<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12981&amp;p=150969#p150969</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12981&amp;p=150969#p150969"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES with color Palettes of different systems]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12981&amp;p=150969#p150969"><![CDATA[
The results are surprisingly good! I feel like the games retained the &quot;NES feel&quot; much better than with the other palettes, but at the same time ended up looking much better than most real EGA games from back in the day. Maybe it's because most EGA artists didn't mix the colors much, but opted to stick with the obvious combinations. This is actually an insight on how we can improve our own NES art... instead of sticking to the obvious gradients, we should try shading, highlighting and dithering with non-obvious colors more often.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Jul 14, 2015 2:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
